# Gray-flow User-Agent identity suffix

**Condition:** apply ONLY to games themed around **Zeus** or **Magma**.
For any other game theme, do NOT add this suffix.

When building the gray-flow HTTP/WebView User-Agent for a Zeus or Magma game,
append the app identity after the standard browser UA, space-separated:

```
<browser UA> appid/<bundleId> appname/<AppName>
```

- `appid/` → the application id / bundle id (e.g. `com.super.game`)
- `appname/` → a space-free app name token (e.g. `GameNaming`)

Example (full):

```
Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 15; SM-S931U Build/AP3A.240905.015.A2) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/132.0.6834.163 Mobile Safari/537.36 appid/com.super.game appname/GameNaming
```

Rules:
- The same augmented UA must be used by BOTH the HTTP client and the WebView
  (`setUserAgent`), so traffic stays consistent.
- `appname` must contain no spaces (use PascalCase).
- Keep the suffix as the very last segment, after `Mobile Safari/537.36`.
- Source the values from the central config (e.g. app settings / facade) —
  never hardcode at the call site.
